				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Like the Wiki says, writing to $4017 has a delayed effect (applied 3 or 4 cycles later, to correspond with an odd cycle?).<br />Writing with bit 7 set to $4017 clocks the half/quarter frames, but does so after the 3/4 cycles delay (this wasn't implemented in my emu).<br />Additionally, it looks like if the frame counter is reset at or around the same time it clocks the half/quarter frames through its normal process, the extra frame clock that is normally caused by a write to $4017 (with the high bit set) does not occur.<br /><br />Implementing both of these behaviors makes Mesen pass all of these tests (1 to 11) - although I am unsure of how accurate my implementation is vs the actual NES.<br /><br />Thanks for making those tests!</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

